    <title>Tensored Segre classes</title>
    <summary>  We study a class obtained from the Segre class $s(Z,Y)$ of an embedding of
schemes by incorporating the datum of a line bundle on $Z$. This class
satisfies basic properties analogous to the ordinary Segre class, but leads to
remarkably simple formulas in standard intersection-theoretic situations such
as excess or residual intersections. We prove a formula for the behavior of
this class under linear joins, and use this formula to prove that a `Segre zeta
function' associated with ideals generated by forms of the same degree is a
rational function.
</summary>
